The mint flavor was too strong for most of my guests. Some likened it to a breath mint! I would try again with a different herb in the ricotta.

Rating: 3
This was a pretty good recipe, but the parm flavor surprised me more than I expected. Boyfriend loved it but wouldn't eat it cold, I tend to agree that chilled I think cream cheese might go better with the mint. Served warm it's beautiful.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe kind of the fly with what I had in my fridge. I ended up substituting fresh sage for the mint and using dried parsley. It was delicious! I didn't even let them chill all of the way and they were really tasty. I think you could substitute all kinds of herbs for the mint!! Will definitely make again.

