This sounds delicious, but it also sounds like an updated, modernized, version of blintzes!! Sliced and served cold. I will try it.

Rating: 3
Fabulous! I made this for a brunch and everyone gobbled it up. I double the egg mixture and then did one and a half times the filling for 8 people. It's a very simple recipe and it's quite easy to do ahead of time.

Rating: 4
So yummy! Just really tasty to have cold with other brunch items. I did change a few things. I added an extra egg and some cream to the egg mixture, because 3 eggs didn't seem enough. I also made the filling with almost 2 cups of ricotta and parm mixed with the romano cheese. Lots of mint! The filling was delicious on its own...

Rating: 2
Made this last night for a group of women. It was easy, but the consensus was that the filling was the tastiest part & would be better rolled in a tortilla or wrap (and much less time consuming).